1969 VINTAGE

At the Hospices de Beaune auction of the 1969 vintage in Burgundy 305 barrels were bid—one half the normal quantity. The prices were the highest in history, reflecting the intrinsic excellence of the wine. Now, almost two years after that famous auction, the 1969 Burgundies are beginning to arrive in this country and it is apparent that those who bought early were extremely fortunate. The wines are big, deep, and very long-lived in the classical style of great Burgundies. They will equal, if not surpass in quality the 1961 vintage—the greatest af the past decade. Due to scarcity, we can project that these wines will be selling at astronomical ‘price levels two-three years from now if. indeed, they are available at all. We strongly urge Burgundy lovers to consider acquiring the classic 1969 Burgundies now, while avail- ability remains. Because of the uncertainty caused by the dock strike, our vast array of great 1969 red Burgundies have been de- ferred for shipment until the Spring of 1972. Those listed below are available for immediate delivery to those who want to experience the greatness of 1969 Burgundies.
